\nAusterity and celibacy "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nare the waterless bath. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nThere are six holes in the world, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwhere one’s wealth leaks out: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nlaziness and negligence, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nlack of initiative and lack of restraint, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nsleepiness and sloth. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nYou should completely get rid of these holes!”"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"style":"text-align:center"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN1/issariya-sutta/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SN.1.77. Issariya Sutta (“Authority”)"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"excerpt":"“What gets old, what doesn’t get old? \nWhat’s called a deviation? \nWhat’s a roadblock for skillful qualities? \nWhat is ending day and night…","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"type":"text","title":"Saṁyutta Nikāya (\"The Linked Discourses\")","userDate":null,"date":null,"tags":null,"excerpt":"SN.1.76. Najīrati Sutta (\"Getting Old\")","parentPath":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/","picture":null,"author":[""]}},"relatedPosts":{"totalCount":0,"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"slu